# Delivery Discipline

Before every user-facing delivery in `assemblymes`, always follow this order:

1. Self-check first.
2. Run a production-oriented build check before delivery whenever code changed.
3. Verify the affected flow or behavior before delivery.
4. Only then deliver the result to the user.

Non-negotiable requirements:

- Never skip self-check, build, or verification before handing off code changes.
- Treat this as a highest-priority project rule regardless of which underlying model is active.
- If a build or verification fails, fix the issue first or clearly report the blocking failure with logs and root cause.
- Do not present work as complete until the above discipline has been followed.
